AD_FIELD.NAME: EM_Etmeta_Payscript Logic
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Field to describe a compatible payscript logic
AD_FIELD.HELP: Field to describe a compatible payscript logic to adapt business logic of legacy javascript linked to static smartclient.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Organization
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Organizational entity within client
AD_FIELD.HELP: An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Description
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Detailed explanation of the button functionality
AD_FIELD.HELP: Provides a comprehensive description of what the button does when clicked. This field is used for documentation purposes and may be displayed in extended tooltips or help systems. It should explain the button''s purpose, expected behavior, and any prerequisites for its use

AD_FIELD.NAME: Custom Javascript
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: JavaScript code for customizing the field in the new UI.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Defines custom JavaScript that the new UI will interpret to modify the fieldâ€™s behavior or appearance.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Action Handler
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Custom JavaScript or server-side logic for button execution
AD_FIELD.HELP: Contains custom code or configuration that defines specific behavior when the button is clicked. This can include JavaScript functions, server-side process calls, or configuration parameters. Leave empty to use the default behavior defined by the button type and action fields.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Label
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Unique identifier key for programmatic reference
AD_FIELD.HELP: A unique alphanumeric identifier used to reference this button programmatically. This key remains constant even if the display name changes, making it suitable for API calls, custom code integration, and configuration management. Should follow naming conventions using uppercase letters and underscores.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Sequence
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Order of appearance within the toolbar section
AD_FIELD.HELP: Determines the display order of buttons within their assigned toolbar section. Lower numbers appear first (left to right). Buttons with the same sequence number are ordered alphabetically by name. Use increments of 10 to allow for easy insertion of new buttons between existing ones. Each section has an intern section number.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Name
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Display name for the toolbar button
AD_FIELD.HELP: This field defines the text that will be displayed on the toolbar button. It should be concise and clearly indicate the button''s function. The name will appear as button text or tooltip depending on the button configuration

AD_FIELD.NAME: Action
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Predefined action type that the button will execute
AD_FIELD.HELP: Specifies the standard action that will be performed when the button is clicked. Common actions include SAVE, NEW, DELETE, REFRESH, CANCEL, EXPORT, etc. This field works in conjunction with the Button Type to determine the exact behavior. Custom actions can be defined for specialized functionality.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Active
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_FIELD.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Client
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Client for this installation.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Type
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Classification of button behavior and interaction pattern
AD_FIELD.HELP: Defines how the button behaves when clicked and what type of user interface it presents. ACTION buttons execute immediate operations, DROPDOWN buttons show a menu of options, MODAL buttons open dialog windows, TOGGLE buttons switch between states, and CUSTOM buttons implement specialized behavior defined in the action handler.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Icon
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Visual icon representation for the button
AD_FIELD.HELP: Defines the icon that will be displayed on the toolbar button. This can be a base64 encoded image, an emoji, or a reference to an icon from the system icon library. Icons help users quickly identify button functions and improve the user interface experience.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Module
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Module
AD_FIELD.HELP: Indicates the module the element forms part of.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Window
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A work area which can be used to create, view, edit, and process a record.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Window field identifies a unique Window in the system.

AD_FIELD.HELP: Defines a hex code (#RRGGBB) that the new UI will use to display the selected option's color.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Toolbar Section
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Designated area of the toolbar where the button appears
AD_FIELD.HELP: Determines the placement of the button within the toolbar layout. LEFT section typically contains primary actions like New and Save, CENTER section holds secondary actions like Delete and Export, and RIGHT section includes utility functions like Searc Filters and Process. This organization helps maintain consistent user interface patterns across the application.
